## Complete Deployment Guide (From Scratch)

### 1. Connect to EC2
```powershell
ssh -i "C:\Users\ayush\Desktop\ts-ayush.pem" ubuntu@13.233.194.8
```

---

### 2. Install Docker
```bash
sudo apt update -y && sudo apt install docker.io -y
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker
sudo usermod -aG docker ubuntu
newgrp docker
```

---

### 3. Install Docker Compose
```bash
sudo curl -L "https://github.com/docker/compose/releases/latest/download/docker-compose-$(uname -s)-$(uname -m)" -o /usr/local/bin/docker-compose
sudo chmod +x /usr/local/bin/docker-compose
docker-compose --version
```

---

### 4. Clean EC2 (if redeploying)
```bash
cd ~/instagram-main
docker-compose -f docker-compose.production.yml down -v
cd ~
rm -rf ~/instagram-main
```

---

### 5. Upload Project (new PowerShell terminal)
```powershell
scp -i "C:\Users\ayush\Desktop\ts-ayush.pem" -r "C:\Users\ayush\Desktop\instagram-main\instagram-main" ubuntu@13.233.194.8:~/
```

---

### 6. Fix Permissions (back in SSH)
```bash
sudo chmod -R 777 ~/instagram-main/backend/migrations
sudo chmod -R 755 ~/instagram-main/
```

---

### 7. Deploy
```bash
cd ~/instagram-main
docker-compose -f docker-compose.production.yml up -d --build
```

---

### 8. Check Status
```bash
docker-compose -f docker-compose.production.yml ps
```

---

### 9. Visit App
```
http://13.233.194.8
```

---

## Useful Commands
```bash
# View all logs
docker-compose -f docker-compose.production.yml logs -f

# View specific service logs
docker-compose -f docker-compose.production.yml logs -f postgres
docker-compose -f docker-compose.production.yml logs -f backend
docker-compose -f docker-compose.production.yml logs -f frontend

# Stop everything
docker-compose -f docker-compose.production.yml down

# Restart everything
docker-compose -f docker-compose.production.yml restart

# Check running containers
docker ps
```